government troops and opponents of leader  Muammar Qaddafi  has
left 6,000 people dead, the rebel forces spokesman, Colonel
Abdullah Al Mahdi, said on Al Jazeera television today. Al
Mahdi, who defected from Qaddafiâ€™s military, said the rebels
